ENTRY       EC 2.1.3.12                 Enzyme
NAME        decarbamoylnovobiocin carbamoyltransferase;
            novN (gene name)
CLASS       Transferases;
            Transferring one-carbon groups;
            Carboxy- and carbamoyltransferases
SYSNAME     carbamoyl phosphate:decarbamoylnovobiocin 3''-O-carbamoyltransferase
REACTION    carbamoyl phosphate + decarbamoylnovobiocin = phosphate + novobiocin [RN:R06772]
ALL_REAC    R06772
SUBSTRATE   carbamoyl phosphate [CPD:C00169];
            decarbamoylnovobiocin
PRODUCT     phosphate [CPD:C00009];
            novobiocin [CPD:C05080]
COMMENT     The enzyme catalyses the last step in the biosynthesis of the aminocoumarin antibiotic novobiocin. The reaction is activated by ATP [1].
